title: Why Didn't God Punish Jesus Longer? A Problem For Penal Substitution
description:
Penal substitution claims that Christ was punished in our place. As a result, we don't have to spend eternity in hell. However, how can this be the case when Jesus didn't spend eternity in hell, which is supposedly my deserved punishment? Advocates of penal substitution claim that this is possible because Christ had infinite dignity, which allowed him to suffer the infinite punishment in a finite period of time. In this video, I attack this response and show that it is at best vague and at worst backfires against PSA.

Link to my book: https://www.amazon.com/Devils-Disbarment-Exploring-Christs-Victory-ebook/dp/B0CWB89MXM
